WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.031
Leading geographically dispersed, virtual teams introduces friction known as social

00:00:05.031 --> 00:00:10.062
distance. The SPLIT framework identifies five components that create this

00:00:10.062 --> 00:00:15.093
distance. Consider a worked example of a virtual team. First,

00:00:15.093 --> 00:00:20.124
the Structure of reporting lines becomes obscured without physical proximity.

00:00:20.124 --> 00:00:25.156
This leads to a breakdown in Process, where workflows lose

00:00:25.156 --> 00:00:30.187
clarity and cause delays. Next, Language differences hinder mutual understanding.

00:00:30.187 --> 00:00:35.218
This weakens the shared Identity and purpose. Finally, reliance on

00:00:35.218 --> 00:00:40.249
Technology amplifies feelings of disconnection. The mandate is to mitigate

00:00:40.249 --> 00:00:45.280
this distance by maintaining frequent, brief contact to validate contributions.
